2)
<?php
echo "    1    2     3\n";
for ($i = 1; $i <= 3; $i++) {
    echo "$i  "; // Print row label
    for ($j = 1; $j <= 3; $j++) { 
        $result = $i / $j;
        $formatted = rtrim(rtrim(number_format($result, 2), '0'), '.');
        printf("%-5s", $formatted);
    }
    echo "\n";
}
?>

OUTPUT
   1    2     3
1  1    0.5  0.33 
2  2    1    0.67 
3  3    1.5  1    

4)
Predict the output of the following snippet:
$animal = “antelope”; $animal_heads = 1; $animal_legs = 4;
echo“The $animal has $animal_heads head(s).”;
echo“The $animal has $animal_legs leg(s).”;

OUTPUT:
